            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Brush the ends of the cut sausage roll with a little <strong>cold water </strong>and join the two ends together to form a circle</p><p>Gently twist each section, without tearing it from the main body, so it is filling-side up, then brush the pastry with <strong>cold water </strong>and sprinkle over your <strong>fennel seeds</strong> – this is your <strong>pork & leek sausage roll wreath</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30-35 min or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the pastry is until golden, cooked through and the edges have puffed up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
