        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the wreath is cooking, cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining chicken stock mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>chicken salt chips</strong></p>",
